The paper deals with the design of neural network architectures, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on optimizing the architecture to satisfy resource constraints, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The paper also mentions the use of reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under cs.NE. Finally, the paper adapts algorithms from discrete optimization, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY).
